frameDefinitions: An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.

The Becoming_detached frame covers two situations: a scene in which one thing comes to be physically detached from something else; or a scene in which two things come to be disconnected from each other.
In this frame a Source_emitter discharges its Emission along a Path or to a Goal.  ' (1)
An Agent causes a Firearm to discharge which induces the rapid motion of the Projectile.
A Cause leads to the formation of a Created_entity.
In this frame an Emission emanates from a Source along a Path or to a Goal.
frameExamples: After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
The ship became <t>decoupled</t> from the dock.
(1) The factory <t>exudes</t> toxic fumes from three large chimneys.
The bank robber <t>shot</t> at the clerks with an AK-47.
listRoleDefinitions: This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor responsible for starting the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role is for the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.
This role identifies the <fen>Item</fen> that detaches from the <fen>Source</fen>.
<fen>Source</fen> identifies the location to which an <fen>Item</fen> was attached before getting detached.

This role identifies the plural <fen>Items</fen> that are becoming detached from each other, resulting in their separation.


Notice that when the role <fen>Items</fen> occurs, neither <fen>Item</fen> nor <fen>Source</fen> can occur.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Item</fen> becomes detached from the <fen>Source</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Item</fen>  becomes detached.
The <fen>Source_emitter</fen> is the item  from which the <fen>Emission</fen> are discharged.
The <fen>Emission</fen>s are discharged out of the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> .
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> emits the <fen>Emission</fen>.
The entity whose rapid, dangerous motion is caused by the Agent and/or Firearm.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act causing the motion of the Projectile.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the shooting event takes place.
The location in which the shooting event takes place.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces an effect. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
The <fen>Creator</fen> creates a created entity.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
The <fen>Emission</fen>s are discharged out of the <fen>Source</fen> .
The <fen>Source</fen> is the location from which the <fen>Emission</fen> emanates.
This role identifies the time when the emanation occurs.
listRoleExamples: The robbers shot at the clerks <fex>as they ran out of the bank</fex>
The bankrobbers were crazy enough to shoot at the clerks with an AK-47 <fex>inside the bank</fex>
